block.original:
Gekk meirr at þatmiþrar brautar;

kvam hann at hu`si,hurþ vas a` ga_e`tti;

inn nam ganga,eldr vas a` golfi,

hjo`n so~`tu þarho~`r at arni.

Ai ok Eddaaldinfalda.

Jo`þ o`l Edda,jo`su vatni,

sveip ho~rvi konaho~rundsvartan;

he`tu Þra_e`l

block.translation:
A son bore Edda,with water they sprinkled him,

With a cloth his hairso black they covered;

Thræll they named him,

block.original:
Gekk Ri`gr at þatre`ttar brautir;

kvam hann at ho~llu,hurþ vas a` ski`þi;

inn nam ganga,eldr vas a` golfi:

Afi ok Ammao~`ttu hu`s.

block.translation:
The woman satand the distaff wielded,

At the weaving with armsoutstretched she worked;

On her head was a band,on her breast a smock;

On her shoulders a kerchiefwith clasps there was.

Home did they bringthe bride for Karl,

In goatskins clad,and keys she bore;

Snör was her name,'neath the veil she sat;

A home they made ready,and rings exchanged,

The bed they decked,and a dwelling made.

block.original:
Klo`k nam fogla,kyrra elda,

sefa of svefja,sorgir la_e`gja;



afl ok eljuna`tta manna.

block.translation:
Bird-chatter learned he,flames could he lessen.,

Minds could quiet,and sorrows calm;



The might and strengthof twice four men.
